ed yet.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Confirmed","id":"10001","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"components":[],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"Today we feel that {{euca-install-image}} can be a bit more intelligent so that it knows what is given to it as an input. Just had a face palm moment where I gave a {{xz file}} to it and it went ahead and bundled/uploaded/registered an EMI out of it which failed to boot on the node controller with an error message:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n2015-06-27 23:14:10 ERROR 000017439 copy_creator             | [i-688c54fa] failed to clone/copy blob emi-4fa925ed-6908f48b to blob AID5YDF0SC6PSSLWXTCIZ/i-688c54fa/emi-4fa925ed-6908f48b: 7 blobstore.c:4244 one of the source blockblobs is too small for the map\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nWe feel that {{libguestfs}} can be utilized inside {{installimage.py}} to first verify the files given to it as input and appropriately error out in the beginning itself.\r\n\r\nHope this makes sense, please let me know if you have any questions.\r\n\r\nCheers,\r\nDeependra","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"Bundling commands should warn when given unexpected file types","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=dshekhawat","name":"dshekhawat","key":"dshekhawat","accountId":"557058:dc10d216-39f8-4d84-a5ff-7d4daf8a44ed","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/7cda271db1cec24c198fdfb42ec8a8ae?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Ddshekhawat%26avatarId%3D15400%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com